iles/*path (GET)  ││ │\n  Line 86: │ files    │    │ Generate │    │    - Parse JWT with RS256         │\n  Line 92: │          │    │          │    │    - Multipart: extract path+file │\n  Line 107: │ files/   │    │ Generate │    │ 2. DownloadFileHandler:           │\n  Line 122: ### FileInfo (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n  Line 133: ### UploadFileRequest (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n  Line 138:     Content string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"` // Base64-encoded file content\n  Line 139:     Mode    string `json:\"mode\"`                       // Optional octal file mode (e.g., \"0755\")\n  Line 143: ### FileEntry (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n  Line 147:     Name     string    `json:\"name\"`     // Entry name (filename or directory name)\n  Line 155: ### ListFilesResponse (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n  Line 159:     Files []FileEntry `json:\"files\"` // Array of file/directory entries\n  Line 181: | `maxFileMode` | `0777` | `files.go` | Maximum file mode permission (prevent setuid/setgid) |\n  Line 182: | `defaultFileMode` | `0644` | `files.go` | Default file mode when mode invalid/empty |\n  Line 198: | `/api/files` | POST | JWT | `UploadFileHandler` | Upload file (multipart or JSON) |\n  Line 199: | `/api/files` | GET | JWT | `ListFilesHandler` | List directory contents |\n  Line 200: | `/api/files/*path` | GET | JWT | `DownloadFileHandler` | Download file |\n  Line 204: **Endpoint**: `POST /api/files`\n  Line 223: | `content` | `string` | Yes | Base64-encoded file content |\n  Line 224: | `mode` | `string` | No | Octal file mode (default: 0644, max: 0777) |\n  Line 237: - 400 Bad Request: Missing path/file, invalid Base64, path escape, invalid mode\n  Line 243: **Endpoint**: `POST /api/files`\n  Line 253: | `file` | `file` | Yes | File content |\n  Line 254: | `mode` | `string` | No | Octal file mode |\n  Line 260: **Endpoint**: `GET /api/files?path=<directory>`\n  Line 272:     \"files\": [\n  Line 299: **Endpoint**: `GET /api/files/<path>`\n  Line 308: | `Content-Type` | MIME type | Detected from file extension (fallback: `application/octet-stream`) |\n  Line 309: | `Content-Disposition` | `attachment; filename=\"<filename>\"` | Download prompt |\n  Line 347: | 500 Internal Server Error | Directory read failure, file write failure, parent directory creation failure, stat failure |\n  Line 372: | Missing file (multipart) | 400 | `\"missing file\"` |\n  Line 376: | File mode > 0777 | 400 | `\"invalid file mode\"` |\n  Line 378: | File write failure | 500 | `\"failed to write file\"` |\n  Line 379: | Stat failure after write | 500 | `\"failed to get file info\"` |\n  Line 394: | Path is directory | 400 | `\"path is not a file\"` |\n  Line 395: | File not found | 404 | `\"file not found\"` |\n  Line 396: | Stat failure | 500 | `\"failed to stat file\"` |\n  Line 408: | Multipart upload | form-data with path=\"upload.txt\", file content | HTTP 200, FileInfo returned, file written |\n  Line 413: | Mode > 0777 | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"test\", \"mode\": \"1000\"}` | HTTP 400, \"invalid file mode\" |\n  Line 414: | Parent directory creation | `{\"path\": \"new/dir/file.txt\", \"content\": \"test\"}` | HTTP 200, parents created with 0755 |\n  Line 416: | Multipart missing file | form-data without file field | HTTP 400, \"missing file\" |\n  Line 417: | File open failure (multipart) | Invalid form file | HTTP 500, \"failed to open file\" |\n  Line 418: | File read failure (multipart) | Read error on form file | HTTP 500, \"failed to read file\" |\n  Line 424: | List valid directory | `GET /api/files?path=testdir` (with files) | HTTP 200, FileEntry array |\n  Line 425: | List empty directory | `GET /api/files?path=emptydir` | HTTP 200, empty files array |\n  Line 426: | Missing path parameter | `GET /api/files` | HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\" |\n  Line 427: | Path escape | `GET /api/files?path=../escape` | HTTP 400, \"invalid path\" |\n  Line 428: | Non-existent directory | `GET /api/files?path=nonexistent` | HTTP 500, \"failed to read directory\" |\n  Line 435: | Download existing file | `GET /api/files/testfile.txt` | HTTP 200, file content, correct headers |\n  Line 436: | Download with extension | `GET /api/files/data.json` | Content-Type: application/json |\n  Line 437: | Unknown extension | `GET /api/files/data.xyz` | Content-Type: application/octet-stream |\n  Line 438: | Leading slash stripped | `GET /api/files//absolute.txt` | Resolved correctly |\n  Line 439: | Path escape | `GET /api/files/../escape.txt` | HTTP 400, \"invalid path\" |\n  Line 440: | File not found | `GET /api/files/nonexistent.txt` | HTTP 404, \"file not found\" |\n  Line 441: | Path is directory | `GET /api/files/subdir` | HTTP 400, \"path is not a file\" |\n  Line 442: | Symlink inside workspace | Symlink pointing within workspace | Resolved to target file |\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 921 matches (821 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":921,"truncated":true},"title":"file|delete|rename|mkdir","time":{"start":1775862707933,"end":1775862707960}}}}
