{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862713368,"sessionID":"ses_286572f10ffeSFQ2dtrLqZNTfc","part":{"id":"prt_d79aa88ae0013Mi4tmoAbHVjsq","messageID":"msg_d79aa772a0012mfzVR4qusDRhH","sessionID":"ses_286572f10ffeSFQ2dtrLqZNTfc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a97b8d11bab9460ea8b5e1798765c54b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: PicoD File Management API provides secure file operations within sandbox pods. It exposes REST endpoints for uploading, listing, and downloading files with workspace jail enforcement, path traversal protection, Base64/multipart upload support, and RS256 JWT authentication. The file API enables AI agents and code interpreters to manage workspace files safely within the sandbox boundary.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### System Context\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                     Kubernetes Cluster                               │\n24: │  ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────────────────┐│\n25: │  │   Router    │────▶│  Workload   │────▶│      Sandbox Pod        ││\n26: │  │ Deployment  │     │   Manager   │     │ ┌─────────────────────┐ ││\n27: │  │             │     │             │     │ │      PicoD          │ ││\n28: │  │ JWTManager  │     │ Creates     │     │ │  ┌───────────────┐  │ ││\n29: │  │ (Private    │     │ Pod +       │     │ │  │ Files API     │  │ ││\n30: │  │  Key)       │     │ Inject      │     │ │  │               │  │ ││\n31: │  │             │     │ Public Key  │     │ │  │ UploadFile    │  │ ││\n32: │  │             │     │ via Env Var │     │ │  │ ListFiles     │  │ ││\n33: │  │             │     │             │     │ │  │ DownloadFile  │  │ ││\n34: │  │             │     │             │     │ │  └───────────────┘  │ ││\n35: │  │             │     │             │     │ │      Workspace      │ ││\n36: │  │             │     │             │     │ │      (Jail Root)    │ ││\n37: │  └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘     │ └─────────────────────┘ ││\n38: │         │                                 └─────────────────────────┘│\n39: │         │ JWT Token (RS256)                                          │\n40: │         ▼                                                            │\n41: │  ┌─────────────┐                                                    │\n42: │  │   Client    │────▶ Router Proxy ────▶ PicoD /api/files          │\n43: │  │  (SDK/CLI)  │                                                    │\n44: │  └─────────────┘                                                    │\n45: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n46: ```\n47: \n48: ### Component Diagram\n49: \n50: ```\n51: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n52: │                         PicoD Server                                 │\n53: │ ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────────────┐ │\n54: │ │   Config    │  │   AuthManager   │  │      Gin Engine           │ │\n55: │ │ ┌─────────┐ │  │ ┌─────────────┐ │  │ ┌─────────────────────────┐│ │\n56: │ │ │ Port    │ │  │ │ publicKey   │ │  │ │ Logger Middleware       ││ │\n57: │ │ │Workspace│ │  │ │ mutex       │ │  │ │ Recovery Middleware     ││ │\n58: │ │ └─────────┘ │  │ └─────────────┘ │  │ │ AuthMiddleware          ││ │\n59: │ └─────────────┘  │ AuthMiddleware  │  │ │                         ││ │\n60: │                  │ LoadPublicKey   │  │ │ /api/files (POST/GET)   ││ │\n61: │                  └─────────────────┘  │ │ /api/files/*path (GET)  ││ │\n62: │                                       │ └─────────────────────────┐│ │\n63: │                                       └───────────────────────────┘ │\n64: │ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n65: │ │                      sanitizePath                                │ │\n66: │ │   Workspace Jail: symlink resolution, path traversal prevention │ │\n67: │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n68: │ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n69: │ │                   File Operations                                │ │\n70: │ │   Upload: JSON (Base64) or multipart, parent dir creation        │ │\n71: │ │   List:   os.ReadDir with FileEntry metadata extraction          │ │\n72: │ │   Download: MIME type detection, Content-Disposition header      │ │\n73: │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n74: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n75: ```\n76: \n77: ### Request Flow\n78: \n79: ```\n80: File Upload Request:\n81: ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌───────────────────────────────────┐\n82: │  Client  │───▶│  Router  │───▶│            PicoD                  │\n83: │          │    │          │    │                                   │\n84: │ POST     │    │ Validate │    │ 1. AuthMiddleware:                │\n85: │ /api/    │    │ Session  │    │    - Extract Bearer token         │\n86: │ files    │    │ Generate │    │    - Parse JWT with RS256         │\n87: │          │    │ JWT      │    │    - Validate expiration          │\n88: │          │    │          │    │    - Apply MaxBytesReader         │\n89: │          │    │          │    │                                   │\n90: │          │    │          │    │ 2. UploadFileHandler:             │\n91: │          │    │          │    │    - Detect content-type          │\n92: │          │    │          │    │    - Multipart: extract path+file │\n93: │          │    │          │    │    - JSON: decode Base64 content  │\n94: │          │    │          │    │    - sanitizePath(path)           │\n95: │          │    │          │    │    - parseFileMode(mode)          │\n96: │          │    │          │    │    - MkdirAll parent dirs         │\n97: │          │    │          │    │    - WriteFile content            │\n98: │          │    │          │    │    - Return FileInfo              │\n99: └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └───────────────────────────────────┘\n100: \n101: File Download Request:\n102: ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌───────────────────────────────────┐\n103: │  Client  │───▶│  Router  │───▶│            PicoD                  │\n104: │          │    │          │    │                                   │\n105: │ GET      │    │ Validate │    │ 1. AuthMiddleware                 │\n106: │ /api/    │    │ Session  │    │                                   │\n107: │ files/   │    │ Generate │    │ 2. DownloadFileHandler:           │\n108: │ <path>   │    │ JWT      │    │    - Extract wildcard path param  │\n109: │          │    │          │    │    - Trim leading \"/\"             │\n110: │          │    │          │    │    - sanitizePath(path)           │\n111: │          │    │          │    │    - os.Stat (check exists+type)  │\n112: │          │    │          │    │    - MIME type by extension       │\n113: │          │    │          │    │    - Content-Disposition header   │\n114: │          │    │          │    │    - c.File(sanitizedPath)        │\n115: └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └───────────────────────────────────┘\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## Data Structures\n121: \n122: ### FileInfo (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n123: \n124: ```go\n125: type FileInfo struct {\n126:     Path     string    `json:\"path\"`     // Relative path from workspace\n127:     Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`     // File size in bytes\n128:     Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`     // File mode as octal string (e.g., \"0644\")\n129:     Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"` // Last modification time\n130: }\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ### UploadFileRequest (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n134: \n135: ```go\n136: type UploadFileRequest struct {\n137:     Path    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`    // Destination path (relative to workspace)\n138:     Content string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"` // Base64-encoded file content\n139:     Mode    string `json:\"mode\"`                       // Optional octal file mode (e.g., \"0755\")\n140: }\n141: ```\n142: \n143: ### FileEntry (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n144: \n145: ```go\n146: type FileEntry struct {\n147:     Name     string    `json:\"name\"`     // Entry name (filename or directory name)\n148:     Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`     // Entry size in bytes\n149:     Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"` // Last modification time\n150:     Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`     // Entry mode as octal string\n151:     IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`   // Whether entry is a directory\n152: }\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ### ListFilesResponse (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n156: \n157: ```go\n158: type ListFilesResponse struct {\n159:     Files []FileEntry `json:\"files\"` // Array of file/directory entries\n160:     Path  string      `json:\"path\"`  // Directory path (relative to workspace)\n161: }\n162: ```\n163: \n164: ### Server (`pkg/picod/server.go`)\n165: \n166: ```go\n167: type Server struct {\n168:     config      *Config               // Server configuration\n169:     engine      *gin.Engine           // Gin HTTP framework\n170:     httpServer  *http.Server          // Underlying HTTP server\n171:     authManager *AuthManager          // JWT authentication manager\n172:     workspace   string                // Resolved workspace directory (absolute path)\n173:     startTime   time.Time             // Server start time for uptime tracking\n174: }\n175: ```\n176: \n177: ### Constants\n178: \n179: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n180: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n181: | `maxFileMode` | `0777` | `files.go` | Maximum file mode permission (prevent setuid/setgid) |\n182: | `defaultFileMode` | `0644` | `files.go` | Default file mode when mode invalid/empty |\n183: | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | `auth.go` | Environment variable for PEM public key |\n184: | `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` (32 MiB) | `auth.go` | Request body size limit after JWT validation |\n185: | `version` | `\"0.0.1\"` | `health.go` | PicoD version string |\n186: | `service` | `\"PicoD\"` | `health.go` | Service name for health response |\n187: | `readHeaderTimeout` | `10 * time.Second` | `server.go` | HTTP ReadHeaderTimeout |\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ## API Contracts\n192: \n193: ### Endpoints Summary\n194: \n195: | Endpoint | Method | Auth | Handler | Description |\n196: |----------|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n197: | `/health` | GET | No | `HealthCheckHandler` | Server health status |\n198: | `/api/files` | POST | JWT | `UploadFileHandler` | Upload file (multipart or JSON) |\n199: | `/api/files` | GET | JWT | `ListFilesHandler` | List directory contents |\n200: | `/api/files/*path` | GET | JWT | `DownloadFileHandler` | Download file |\n201: \n202: ### Upload File (JSON)\n203: \n204: **Endpoint**: `POST /api/files`\n205: \n206: **Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n207: \n208: **Content-Type**: `application/json`\n209: \n210: **Request Body**:\n211: ```json\n212: {\n213:     \"path\": \"output/result.txt\",\n214:     \"content\": \"SGVsbG8gV29ybGQ=\",  // Base64-encoded\n215:     \"mode\": \"0644\"\n216: }\n217: ```\n218: \n219: **Request Fields**:\n220: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n221: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n222: | `path` | `string` | Yes | Destination path relative to workspace |\n223: | `content` | `string` | Yes | Base64-encoded file content |\n224: | `mode` | `string` | No | Octal file mode (default: 0644, max: 0777) |\n225: \n226: **Response** (200 OK):\n227: ```json\n228: {\n229:     \"path\": \"output/result.txt\",\n230:     \"size\": 11,\n231:     \"mode\": \"0644\",\n232:     \"modified\": \"2026-04-11T10:35:00Z\"\n233: }\n234: ```\n235: \n236: **Error Responses**:\n237: - 400 Bad Request: Missing path/file, invalid Base64, path escape, invalid mode\n238: - 401 Unauthorized: Missing/invalid/expired JWT\n239: - 500 Internal Server Error: Parent directory creation failure, write failure\n240: \n241: ### Upload File (Multipart)\n242: \n243: **Endpoint**: `POST /api/files`\n244: \n245: **Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n246: \n247: **Content-Type**: `multipart/form-data`\n248: \n249: **Form Fields**:\n250: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n251: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n252: | `path` | `string` | Yes | Destination path |\n253: | `file` | `file` | Yes | File content |\n254: | `mode` | `string` | No | Octal file mode |\n255: \n256: **Response** (200 OK): Same as JSON upload\n257: \n258: ### List Files\n259: \n260: **Endpoint**: `GET /api/files?path=<directory>`\n261: \n262: **Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n263: \n264: **Query Parameters**:\n265: | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n266: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n267: | `path` | `string` | Yes | Directory path to list (relative to workspace) |\n268: \n269: **Response** (200 OK):\n270: ```json\n271: {\n272:     \"files\": [\n273:         {\n274:             \"name\": \"src\",\n275:             \"size\": 4096,\n276:             \"modified\": \"2026-04-11T09:00:00Z\",\n277:             \"mode\": \"0755\",\n278:             \"is_dir\": true\n279:         },\n280:         {\n281:             \"name\": \"main.py\",\n282:             \"size\": 1024,\n283:             \"modified\": \"2026-04-11T10:00:00Z\",\n284:             \"mode\": \"0644\",\n285:             \"is_dir\": false\n286:         }\n287:     ],\n288:     \"path\": \"project\"\n289: }\n290: ```\n291: \n292: **Error Responses**:\n293: - 400 Bad Request: Missing path parameter, path traversal detected\n294: - 401 Unauthorized: Missing/invalid/expired JWT\n295: - 500 Internal Server Error: Directory read failure\n296: \n297: ### Download File\n298: \n299: **Endpoint**: `GET /api/files/<path>`\n300: \n301: **Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n302: \n303: **Path Parameter**: File path relative to workspace (wildcard capture `*path`)\n304: \n305: **Response Headers**:\n306: | Header | Value | Description |\n307: |--------|-------|-------------|\n308: | `Content-Type` | MIME type | Detected from file extension (fallback: `application/octet-stream`) |\n309: | `Content-Disposition` | `attachment; filename=\"<filename>\"` | Download prompt |\n310: \n311: **Response**: File content streamed directly via `c.File(sanitizedPath)`\n312: \n313: **Error Responses**:\n314: - 400 Bad Request: Path traversal detected, path is directory\n315: - 401 Unauthorized: Missing/invalid/expired JWT\n316: - 404 Not Found: File does not exist\n317: - 500 Internal Server Error: Stat failure\n318: \n319: ### Health Check\n320: \n321: **Endpoint**: `GET /health`\n322: \n323: **Authentication**: None (public endpoint)\n324: \n325: **Response** (200 OK):\n326: ```json\n327: {\n328:     \"status\": \"ok\",\n329:     \"service\": \"PicoD\",\n330:     \"version\": \"0.0.1\",\n331:     \"uptime\": \"2h30m15s\"\n332: }\n333: ```\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ## Error Handling\n338: \n339: ### HTTP Status Codes\n340: \n341: | Status | Condition |\n342: |--------|-----------|\n343: | 200 OK | Successful operation |\n344: | 400 Bad Request | Invalid request body, missing required fields, path traversal, invalid Base64, invalid mode, path is directory |\n345: | 401 Unauthorized | Missing Authorization header, invalid JWT, expired token, wrong signing method |\n346: | 404 Not Found | File not found for download |\n347: | 500 Internal Server Error | Directory read failure, file write failure, parent directory creation failure, stat failure |\n348: \n349: ### Error Response Format\n350: \n351: ```json\n352: {\n353:     \"error\": \"<error message>\"\n354: }\n355: ```\n356: \n357: ### Authentication Errors\n358: \n359: | Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n360: |-----------|-------------|---------------|\n361: | Missing Authorization header | 401 | `\"missing authorization header\"` |\n362: | Invalid token format | 401 | `\"invalid token format\"` |\n363: | Expired token | 401 | `\"token is expired\"` |\n364: | Non-RSA signing method | 401 | `\"invalid signing method\"` |\n365: | Invalid signature | 401 | `\"invalid signature\"` |\n366: \n367: ### File Upload Errors\n368: \n369: | Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n370: |-----------|-------------|---------------|\n371: | Missing path parameter | 400 | `\"missing path parameter\"` |\n372: | Missing file (multipart) | 400 | `\"missing file\"` |\n373: | Invalid request body | 400 | `\"invalid request body\"` |\n374: | Path traversal detected | 400 | `\"invalid path: path escape detected\"` |\n375: | Invalid Base64 content | 400 | `\"invalid base64 content\"` |\n376: | File mode > 0777 | 400 | `\"invalid file mode\"` |\n377: | Parent directory creation failure | 500 | `\"failed to create parent directories\"` |\n378: | File write failure | 500 | `\"failed to write file\"` |\n379: | Stat failure after write | 500 | `\"failed to get file info\"` |\n380: \n381: ### File List Errors\n382: \n383: | Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n384: |-----------|-------------|---------------|\n385: | Missing path parameter | 400 | `\"missing path parameter\"` |\n386: | Path traversal detected | 400 | `\"invalid path: path escape detected\"` |\n387: | Directory read failure | 500 | `\"failed to read directory\"` |\n388: \n389: ### File Download Errors\n390: \n391: | Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n392: |-----------|-------------|---------------|\n393: | Path traversal detected | 400 | `\"invalid path: path escape detected\"` |\n394: | Path is directory | 400 | `\"path is not a file\"` |\n395: | File not found | 404 | `\"file not found\"` |\n396: | Stat failure | 500 | `\"failed to stat file\"` |\n397: \n398: ---\n399: \n400: ## Testing Strategy\n401: \n402: ### Unit Tests (`pkg/picod/picod_test.go`)\n403: \n404: #### File Upload Tests\n405: \n406: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n407: |-----------|-------|----------|\n408: | Multipart upload | form-data with path=\"upload.txt\", file content | HTTP 200, FileInfo returned, file written |\n409: | JSON Base64 upload | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"dGVzdCBjb250ZW50\"}` | HTTP 200, FileInfo returned, content decoded |\n410: | Invalid Base64 | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"!!invalid\"}` | HTTP 400, \"invalid base64 content\" |\n411: | Path escape | `{\"path\": \"../escape.txt\", \"content\": \"test\"}` | HTTP 400, \"invalid path\" |\n412: | Invalid mode (non-octal) | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"test\", \"mode\": \"9999\"}` | HTTP 200, uses default 0644 |\n413: | Mode > 0777 | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"test\", \"mode\": \"1000\"}` | HTTP 400, \"invalid file mode\" |\n414: | Parent directory creation | `{\"path\": \"new/dir/file.txt\", \"content\": \"test\"}` | HTTP 200, parents created with 0755 |\n415: | Multipart missing path | form-data without path field | HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\" |\n416: | Multipart missing file | form-data without file field | HTTP 400, \"missing file\" |\n417: | File open failure (multipart) | Invalid form file | HTTP 500, \"failed to open file\" |\n418: | File read failure (multipart) | Read error on form file | HTTP 500, \"failed to read file\" |\n419: \n420: #### File List Tests\n421: \n422: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n423: |-----------|-------|----------|\n424: | List valid directory | `GET /api/files?path=testdir` (with files) | HTTP 200, FileEntry array |\n425: | List empty directory | `GET /api/files?path=emptydir` | HTTP 200, empty files array |\n426: | Missing path parameter | `GET /api/files` | HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\" |\n427: | Path escape | `GET /api/files?path=../escape` | HTTP 400, \"invalid path\" |\n428: | Non-existent directory | `GET /api/files?path=nonexistent` | HTTP 500, \"failed to read directory\" |\n429: | Entry info failure | Directory with unreadable entry | Skipped (continue), other entries returned |\n430: \n431: #### File Download Tests\n432: \n433: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n434: |-----------|-------|----------|\n435: | Download existing file | `GET /api/files/testfile.txt` | HTTP 200, file content, correct headers |\n436: | Download with extension | `GET /api/files/data.json` | Content-Type: application/json |\n437: | Unknown extension | `GET /api/files/data.xyz` | Content-Type: application/octet-stream |\n438: | Leading slash stripped | `GET /api/files//absolute.txt` | Resolved correctly |\n439: | Path escape | `GET /api/files/../escape.txt` | HTTP 400, \"invalid path\" |\n440: | File not found | `GET /api/files/nonexistent.txt` | HTTP 404, \"file not found\" |\n441: | Path is directory | `GET /api/files/subdir` | HTTP 400, \"path is not a file\" |\n442: | Symlink inside workspace | Symlink pointing within workspace | Resolved to target file |\n443: \n444: #### Path Sanitization Tests\n445: \n446: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n447: |-----------|-------|----------|\n448: | Valid relative path | `\"subdir/file.txt\"` | Absolute path within workspace |\n449: | Absolute path | `\"/workspace/file.txt\"` | Strips leading `/`, resolves within workspace |\n450: | Path traversal | `\"../escape.txt\"` | Error: path escape detected |\n451: | Deep traversal | `\"subdir/../../escape.txt\"` | Error: path escape detected |\n452: | Existing symlink (safe) | Symlink pointing within workspace | Resolved to target |\n453: | Null byte injection | `\"file\\x00.txt\"` | Cleaned, safe path within workspace |\n454: \n455: #### Authentication Tests\n456: \n457: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n458: |-----------|-------|----------|\n459: | Missing header | No Authorization | HTTP 401, \"missing authorization header\" |\n460: | Invalid format | `Authorization: InvalidFormat` | HTTP 401 |\n461: | Expired token | JWT with expired `exp` | HTTP 401, \"token is expired\" |\n462: | HS256 token | JWT signed with HS256 | HTTP 401, \"invalid signing method\" |\n463: | Valid RS256 token | JWT signed with matching public key | Request proceeds |\n464: \n465: #### File Mode Parsing Tests\n466: \n467: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n468: |-----------|-------|----------|\n469: | Empty mode | `\"\"` | 0644 (default) |\n470: | Invalid (non-octal) | `\"invalid\"` | 0644 (default) |\n471: | Mode > 0777 | `\"1000\"` | Error: \"invalid file mode\" |\n472: | Valid mode | `\"0755\"` | 0755 |\n473: \n474: ### Test Helper Functions\n475: \n476: ```go\n477: func setupTestServer(t *testing.T) *Server       // Creates test server with temp workspace and RSA key\n478: func generateTestJWT(privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey, expired bool) string  // Generates test JWT token\n479: func makeAuthenticatedRequest(t *testing.T, server *Server, method, path string, body io.Reader, contentType string, jwtToken string) *httptest.ResponseRecorder\n480: func encodePublicKeyPEMForTest(key *rsa.PublicKey) string\n481: ```\n482: \n483: ### Integration Tests\n484: \n485: | Test Scenario | Description |\n486: |---------------|-------------|\n487: | Full file lifecycle | Upload file → List directory → Download file → Verify content matches |\n488: | Auth key mismatch | Router uses different key pair → PicoD rejects token |\n489: | Large file upload | File approaching 32 MiB limit |\n490: | Concurrent operations | Multiple upload/download requests in parallel |\n491: \n492: ---\n493: \n494: ## File Structure\n495: \n496: ```\n497: pkg/picod/\n498: ├── config.go           # Config struct definition (Port, Workspace)\n499: ├── server.go           # Server struct, NewServer, Run, Shutdown, route registration\n500: ├── auth.go             # AuthManager, LoadPublicKeyFromEnv, AuthMiddleware\n501: ├── execute.go          # ExecuteRequest, ExecuteResponse, ExecuteHandler (AR-015)\n502: ├── files.go            # FileInfo, UploadFileRequest, FileEntry, ListFilesResponse, file handlers\n503: ├── health.go           # HealthCheckHandler, version/service constants\n504: ├── sanitize.go         # sanitizePath function for workspace jail security\n505: ├── picod_test.go       # Unit tests for all handlers\n506: └── doc.go              # Package documentation\n507: \n508: cmd/picod/\n509: └── main.go             # Entry point with CLI flag parsing, klog initialization\n510: ```\n511: \n512: ---\n513: \n514: ## Dependencies\n515: \n516: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n517: |---------|---------|---------|\n518: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10+ | HTTP framework, route registration, middleware, JSON binding, multipart form handling |\n519: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2+ | JWT parsing, RSA signing method validation, leeway/expiry options |\n520: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Existing | CLI flag registration, structured logging, fatal error handling |\n521: | `crypto/rsa` | Standard | RSA public key type |\n522: | `crypto/x509` | Standard | PKIX public key parsing |\n523: | `encoding/pem` | Standard | PEM block decoding |\n524: | `encoding/base64` | Standard | Base64 decoding for JSON file upload |\n525: | `os` | Standard | File operations: WriteFile, Stat, ReadDir, MkdirAll |\n526: | `path/filepath` | Standard | Path cleaning, symlink resolution, relative path computation, base extraction |\n527: | `mime` | Standard | `mime.TypeByExtension` for download Content-Type |\n528: | `strconv` | Standard | `ParseUint` for octal file mode parsing |\n529: | `strings` | Standard | Path prefix stripping, trimming |\n530: | `time` | Standard | Time handling for FileInfo.Modified |\n531: | `io` | Standard | `io.ReadAll` for multipart file content |\n532: | `mime/multipart` | Standard | Multipart form parsing |\n533: \n534: ---\n535: \n536: ## Implementation Notes\n537: \n538: ### Upload Handler Flow (JSON)\n539: \n540: ```go\n541: func (s *Server) UploadFileHandler(c *gin.Context) {\n542:     contentType := c.ContentType()\n543:     \n544:     // Detect content type\n545:     if contentType == \"multipart/form-data\" {\n546:         // Multipart handling\n547:         path = c.PostForm(\"path\")\n548:         fileHeader, _ := c.FormFile(\"file\")\n549:         file, _ := fileHeader.Open()\n550:         content, _ = io.ReadAll(file)\n551:         modeStr = c.PostForm(\"mode\")\n552:     } else {\n553:         // JSON handling\n554:         var req UploadFileRequest\n555:         c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)\n556:         path = req.Path\n557:         decoded, _ = base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString(req.Content)\n558:         content = decoded\n559:         modeStr = req.Mode\n560:     }\n561:     \n562:     // Sanitize path\n563:     sanitizedPath, err := sanitizePath(s.workspace, path)\n564:     \n565:     // Parse file mode\n566:     mode, err := parseFileMode(modeStr)\n567:     \n568:     // Create parent directories\n569:     parentDir := filepath.Dir(sanitizedPath)\n570:     os.MkdirAll(parentDir, 0755)\n571:     \n572:     // Write file\n573:     os.WriteFile(sanitizedPath, content, mode)\n574:     \n575:     // Return FileInfo\n576:     info, _ := os.Stat(sanitizedPath)\n577:     c.JSON(200, FileInfo{...})\n578: }\n579: ```\n580: \n581: ### List Handler Flow\n582: \n583: ```go\n584: func (s *Server) ListFilesHandler(c *gin.Context) {\n585:     path := c.Query(\"path\")\n586:     \n587:     // Sanitize path\n588:     sanitizedPath, err := sanitizePath(s.workspace, path)\n589:     \n590:     // Read directory\n591:     entries, err := os.ReadDir(sanitizedPath)\n592:     \n593:     // Build FileEntry array\n594:     files := []FileEntry{}\n595:     for _, entry := range entries {\n596:         info, err := entry.Info()\n597:         if err != nil {\n598:             continue  // Skip entries with stat errors\n599:         }\n600:         files = append(files, FileEntry{\n601:             Name:     entry.Name(),\n602:             Size:     info.Size(),\n603:             Modified: info.ModTime(),\n604:             Mode:     fmt.Sprintf(\"%04o\", info.Mode().Perm()),\n605:             IsDir:    entry.IsDir(),\n606:         })\n607:     }\n608:     \n609:     c.JSON(200, ListFilesResponse{Files: files, Path: path})\n610: }\n611: ```\n612: \n613: ### Download Handler Flow\n614: \n615: ```go\n616: func (s *Server) DownloadFileHandler(c *gin.Context) {\n617:     reqPath := c.Param(\"path\")\n618:     reqPath = strings.TrimPrefix(reqPath, \"/\")\n619:     \n620:     // Sanitize path\n621:     sanitizedPath, err := sanitizePath(s.workspace, reqPath)\n622:     \n623:     // Check file exists and is not directory\n624:     info, err := os.Stat(sanitizedPath)\n625:     if info.IsDir() {\n626:         c.JSON(400, gin.H{\"error\": \"path is not a file\"})\n627:         return\n628:     }\n629:     \n630:     // Detect MIME type\n631:     contentType := mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(sanitizedPath))\n632:     if contentType == \"\" {\n633:         contentType = \"application/octet-stream\"\n634:     }\n635:     \n636:     // Set headers\n637:     filename := filepath.Base(sanitizedPath)\n638:     c.Header(\"Content-Type\", contentType)\n639:     c.Header(\"Content-Disposition\", fmt.Sprintf(\"attachment; filename=\\\"%s\\\"\", filename))\n640:     \n641:     // Stream file\n642:     c.File(sanitizedPath)\n643: }\n644: ```\n645: \n646: ### File Mode Parsing\n647: \n648: ```go\n649: func parseFileMode(modeStr string) (os.FileMode, error) {\n650:     if modeStr == \"\" {\n651:         return defaultFileMode, nil  // 0644\n652:     }\n653:     \n654:     mode, err := strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)\n655:     if err != nil {\n656:         return defaultFileMode, nil  // Invalid → use default\n657:     }\n658:     \n659:     if mode > maxFileMode {  // 0777\n660:         return 0, errors.New(\"invalid file mode\")\n661:     }\n662:     \n663:     return os.FileMode(mode), nil\n664: }\n665: ```\n666: \n667: **Mode Constraints**:\n668: - Max value: `0777` (prevents setuid/setgid/sticky bits)\n669: - Invalid/non-octal strings fall back to `0644`\n670: - Mode > `0777` returns error (reject request)\n671: \n672: ### Route Registration Pattern\n673: \n674: ```go\n675: func NewServer(config *Config) (*Server, error) {\n676:     // ...\n677:     engine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n678:     \n679:     api := engine.Group(\"/api\")\n680:     api.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n681:     {\n682:         api.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)   // AR-015\n683:         api.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)  // AR-016\n684:         api.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)    // AR-016\n685:         api.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)  // AR-016\n686:     }\n687:     // ...\n688: }\n689: ```\n690: \n691: ### Path Sanitization Algorithm\n692: \n693: The `sanitizePath` function enforces workspace jail security:\n694: \n695: 1. Resolve workspace directory (follow symlinks to get canonical path)\n696: 2. Clean requested path (`filepath.Clean`)\n697: 3. Strip leading `/` if absolute\n698: 4. Join with workspace root\n699: 5. Check relative path doesn't start with `..` (path traversal)\n700: 6. If path exists, re-validate after symlink resolution\n701: 7. Return resolved, safe absolute path\n702: \n703: ### MIME Type Detection\n704: \n705: Uses `mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(path))`:\n706: - Common extensions: `.json` → `application/json`, `.txt` → `text/plain`\n707: - Unknown extensions: fallback to `application/octet-stream`\n708: \n709: ---\n710: \n711: ## References\n712: \n713: - `changes/AR-015/design.md` — PicoD Execute API design (shared architecture)\n714: - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for sandbox pod configuration\n715: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` — `AuthModePicoD` constant\n716: - `pkg/router/jwt.go` — Router JWT issuance (key pair generation)\n717: - `pkg/router/errors.go` — Router error types pattern\n718: - `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` — HTTP server lifecycle pattern\n719: - [github.com/gin-gonic/gin](https://github.com/gin-gonic/gin) — Gin framework\n720: - [github.com/golang-jwt/jwt](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt) — JWT library\n721: - [Go mime package](https://pkg.go.dev/mime) — MIME type detection\n\n(End of file - total 721 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nPicoD File Management API provides secure file operations within sandbox pods. It exposes REST endpoints for uploading, listing, and downloading files with workspace jail enforcement, path traversal protection, Base64/multipart upload support, and RS256 JWT authentication. The file API enables AI agents and code interpreters to manage workspace files safely within the sandbox boundary.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/design.md","time":{"start":1775862713354,"end":1775862713366}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862713371,"sessionID":"ses_286572f10ffeSFQ2dtrLqZNTfc","part":{"id":"prt_d79aa8bee001m13lTRdI4NjSEF","messageID":"msg_d79aa772a0012mfzVR4qusDRhH","sessionID":"ses_286572f10ffeSFQ2dtrLqZNTfc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-da585c4fae0e4c8c810c0334a97cfd32","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Implementation Verification\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1** Verify `pkg/picod/files.go` structs exist\n20:   - Check: `FileInfo`, `UploadFileRequest`, `FileEntry`, `ListFilesResponse`\n21:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n22:   - Independently verifiable: Structs compile without error\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2** Verify `parseFileMode` function exists\n25:   - Check: Function handles empty, invalid, valid, and >0777 modes\n26:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n27:   - Independently verifiable: Function compiles\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3** Verify `UploadFileHandler` exists\n30:   - Check: Handler supports multipart and JSON/Base64 upload\n31:   - Check: Handler validates path, Base64, mode, creates parent dirs\n32:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n33:   - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n34: \n35: - [ ] **T1.4** Verify `ListFilesHandler` exists\n36:   - Check: Handler validates path, reads directory, builds FileEntry array\n37:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n38:   - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n39: \n40: - [ ] **T1.5** Verify `DownloadFileHandler` exists\n41:   - Check: Handler strips leading slash, validates path, detects MIME type\n42:   - Check: Handler sets Content-Disposition header, streams file\n43:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n44:   - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n45: \n46: - [ ] **T1.6** Verify route registration in `pkg/picod/server.go`\n47:   - Check: `/api/files` POST → UploadFileHandler\n48:   - Check: `/api/files` GET → ListFilesHandler\n49:   - Check: `/api/files/*path` GET → DownloadFileHandler\n50:   - Verify: `grep -n \"api.*files\" pkg/picod/server.go`\n51:   - Independently verifiable: All three routes registered\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ### Phase 2: File Upload Handler Tests\n56: \n57: - [ ] **T2.1** Test multipart upload\n58:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerMultipart` exists and passes\n59:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerMultipart ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n60:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, file written\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T2.2** Test JSON Base64 upload\n63:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerJSON` exists and passes\n64:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerJSON ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n65:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, content decoded\n66: \n67: - [ ] **T2.3** Test invalid Base64 content\n68:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidBase64` exists and passes\n69:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidBase64 ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n70:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid base64 content\"\n71: \n72: - [ ] **T2.4** Test path traversal detection\n73:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerPathEscape` exists and passes\n74:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerPathEscape ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n75:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid path\"\n76: \n77: - [ ] **T2.5** Test invalid file mode (non-octal)\n78:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidMode` exists and passes\n79:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidMode ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n80:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, uses default 0644\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T2.6** Test file mode > 0777\n83:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerModeTooHigh` exists and passes\n84:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerModeTooHigh ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n85:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid file mode\"\n86: \n87: - [ ] **T2.7** Test parent directory creation\n88:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerParentDirectoryCreation` exists and passes\n89:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerParentDirectoryCreation ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n90:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, parents created with 0755\n91: \n92: - [ ] **T2.8** Add test for multipart missing path\n93:   - Create: `TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingPath`\n94:   - Input: multipart form without `path` field\n95:   - Expected: HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\"\n96:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingPath ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n97:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n98: \n99: - [ ] **T2.9** Add test for multipart missing file\n100:   - Create: `TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingFile`\n101:   - Input: multipart form without `file` field\n102:   - Expected: HTTP 400, \"missing file\"\n103:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingFile ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n104:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ### Phase 3: File List Handler Tests\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T3.1** Test valid directory listing\n111:   - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerValidDirectory` exists and passes\n112:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerValidDirectory ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n113:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, FileEntry array\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T3.2** Test missing path parameter\n116:   - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerMissingPath` exists and passes\n117:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerMissingPath ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n118:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\"\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T3.3** Test path traversal detection\n121:   - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerPathEscape` exists and passes\n122:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerPathEscape ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n123:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid path\"\n124: \n125: - [ ] **T3.4** Test non-existent directory\n126:   - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerNonExistent` exists and passes\n127:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerNonExistent ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n128:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 500, \"failed to read directory\"\n129: \n130: - [ ] **T3.5** Add test for empty directory\n131:   - Create: `TestListFilesHandlerEmptyDirectory`\n132:   - Setup: Create empty directory in workspace\n133:   - Expected: HTTP 200, empty `files` array\n134:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerEmptyDirectory ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n135:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ### Phase 4: File Download Handler Tests\n140: \n141: - [ ] **T4.1** Test existing file download\n142:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerExistingFile` exists and passes\n143:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerExistingFile ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n144:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, file content matches\n145: \n146: - [ ] **T4.2** Test leading slash stripped\n147:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerLeadingSlash` exists and passes\n148:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerLeadingSlash ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n149:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, resolved correctly\n150: \n151: - [ ] **T4.3** Test path traversal detection\n152:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerPathEscape` exists and passes\n153:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerPathEscape ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n154:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid path\"\n155: \n156: - [ ] **T4.4** Test file not found\n157:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerNotFound` exists and passes\n158:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerNotFound ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n159:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 404, \"file not found\"\n160: \n161: - [ ] **T4.5** Test path is directory\n162:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerIsDirectory` exists and passes\n163:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerIsDirectory ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n164:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"path is not a file\"\n165: \n166: - [ ] **T4.6** Add test for MIME type detection (.json)\n167:   - Create: `TestDownloadFileHandlerMIMETypeJSON`\n168:   - Setup: Write `data.json` file\n169:   - Expected: HTTP 200, Content-Type: application/json\n170:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerMIMETypeJSON ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n171:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n172: \n173: - [ ] **T4.7** Add test for unknown extension MIME type\n174:   - Create: `TestDownloadFileHandlerMIMETypeUnknown`\n175:   - Setup: Write `data.xyz` file\n176:   - Expected: HTTP 200, Content-Type: application/octet-stream\n177:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerMIMETypeUnknown ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n178:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n179: \n180: - [ ] **T4.8** Add test for symlink inside workspace\n181:   - Create: `TestDownloadFileHandlerSymlinkInsideWorkspace`\n182:   - Setup: Create file, create symlink pointing to file within workspace\n183:   - Expected: HTTP 200, file content from symlink\n184:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerSymlinkInsideWorkspace ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n185:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ### Phase 5: File Mode Parsing Tests\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T5.1** Test empty mode returns default\n192:   - Test: `TestParseFileModeEmpty` exists and passes\n193:   - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeEmpty ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n194:   - Independently verifiable: Returns 0644\n195: \n196: - [ ] **T5.2** Test invalid mode returns default\n197:   - Test: `TestParseFileModeInvalid` exists and passes\n198:   - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeInvalid ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n199:   - Independently verifiable: Returns 0644\n200: \n201: - [ ] **T5.3** Test mode > 0777 returns error\n202:   - Test: `TestParseFileModeTooHigh` exists and passes\n203:   - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeTooHigh ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n204:   - Independently verifiable: Returns error \"invalid file mode\"\n205: \n206: - [ ] **T5.4** Test valid mode parsing\n207:   - Test: `TestParseFileModeValid` exists and passes\n208:   - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeValid ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n209:   - Independently verifiable: Returns correct FileMode\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ### Phase 6: Integration Tests\n214: \n215: - [ ] **T6.1** Test full file lifecycle\n216:   - Create: `TestFileLifecycle`\n217:   - Steps: Upload file → List directory → Download file → Verify content\n218:   - Verify: `go test -run TestFileLifecycle ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n219:   - Independently verifiable: All operations succeed, content matches\n220: \n221: - [ ] **T6.2** Test large file upload (near 32 MiB limit)\n222:   - Create: `TestUploadLargeFile`\n223:   - Setup: Generate file ~30 MiB\n224:   - Expected: HTTP 200, file written\n225:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadLargeFile ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n226:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T6.3** Test concurrent operations\n229:   - Create: `TestConcurrentFileOperations`\n230:   - Setup: Multiple upload/download requests in parallel\n231:   - Expected: All succeed without race conditions\n232:   - Verify: `go test -race -run TestConcurrentFileOperations ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n233:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes with race detector\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ### Phase 7: Validation and Linting\n238: \n239: - [ ] **T7.1** Run `go vet` on picod package\n240:   - Run: `go vet ./pkg/picod/... ./cmd/picod/...`\n241:   - Verify: No warnings\n242:   - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n243: \n244: - [ ] **T7.2** Run `golangci-lint` on picod package\n245:   - Run: `golangci-lint run ./pkg/picod/... ./cmd/picod/...`\n246:   - Verify: No errors\n247:   - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n248: \n249: - [ ] **T7.3** Run all tests with race detector\n250:   - Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/... -race -v`\n251:   - Verify: All tests pass\n252:   - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n253: \n254: - [ ] **T7.4** Verify test coverage ≥ 80%\n255:   - Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out`\n256:   - Run: `go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep total`\n257:   - Independently verifiable: Coverage ≥ 80%\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ### Phase 8: Binary Validation\n262: \n263: - [ ] **T8.1** Build picod binary\n264:   - Run: `go build -o picod ./cmd/picod/`\n265:   - Verify: Binary exists\n266:   - Independently verifiable: `ls picod`\n267: \n268: - [ ] **T8.2** Run binary with test public key\n269:   - Setup: Generate RSA key pair\n270:   - Setup: Set `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var\n271:   - Run: `./picod -port=8080 -workspace=/tmp/test`\n272:   - Call: `/health` endpoint\n273:   - Expected: HTTP 200 response\n274:   - Independently verifiable: Server starts and responds\n275: \n276: - [ ] **T8.3** Test file upload via binary\n277:   - Setup: Server running with valid JWT\n278:   - Call: `POST /api/files` with JSON upload\n279:   - Expected: HTTP 200, FileInfo returned\n280:   - Independently verifiable: File created in workspace\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## Acceptance Criteria\n285: \n286: - [ ] `pkg/picod/files.go` contains FileInfo, UploadFileRequest, FileEntry, ListFilesResponse structs\n287: - [ ] `parseFileMode` handles empty/invalid/valid/>0777 modes correctly\n288: - [ ] `UploadFileHandler` supports multipart and JSON/Base64 upload\n289: - [ ] `UploadFileHandler` validates path, Base64, mode, creates parent directories\n290: - [ ] `ListFilesHandler` validates path, reads directory, returns FileEntry array\n291: - [ ] `DownloadFileHandler` validates path, detects MIME type, streams file\n292: - [ ] All three file routes registered in server.go\n293: - [ ] All file handler tests pass\n294: - [ ] Path traversal protection works for upload, list, download\n295: - [ ] File mode validation prevents setuid/setgid bits (max 0777)\n296: - [ ] Pass `go vet`\n297: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint`\n298: - [ ] Test coverage ≥ 80%\n299: - [ ] Binary runs with JWT auth and handles file operations\n300: \n301: ---\n302: \n303: ## File Changes Summary\n304: \n305: | File | Action | Lines Changed |\n306: |------|--------|---------------|\n307: | `pkg/picod/files.go` | Existing | ~230 lines |\n308: | `pkg/picod/server.go` | Existing | Routes at lines 71-73 |\n309: | `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Modify | +~60 lines (new tests) |\n310: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | Existing | ~35 lines |\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## Implementation Notes\n315: \n316: - File upload supports both `multipart/form-data` and `application/json` (Base64 encoded)\n317: - Path sanitization via `sanitizePath` enforces workspace jail security\n318: - File mode parsing: `strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)` for octal, max 0777\n319: - MIME type detection: `mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(path))`\n320: - Content-Disposition header: `attachment; filename=\"<filename>\"`\n321: - Parent directories created with 0755 mode\n322: - Default file mode: 0644\n\n(End of file - total 322 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Implementation Verification\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Verify `pkg/picod/files.go` structs exist\n  - Check: `FileInfo`, `UploadFileRequest`, `FileEntry`, `ListFilesResponse`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775862713357,"end":1775862713369}}}}
